body:
PLAGIARIUS. Lat. In the civil law.
A man-stealer; a kidnapper. Dig. 48, 15, 1;
4 Bl. Comm. 219.

POLITICS. The science of government;
the art or practice of administering public
affairs.

POMARIUM.
pear-tree;

In old pleading. An apple orchard.

POST-FACTUM, or
An after-act;
post-act.

PRIME, v. To stand first or paramount;
to take precedence or priority of; to outrank; as, in the sentence “taxes prime all
other liens.”
